&quot;I knew it wouldn't take long before your Olympians would tear things up in my life again,&quot; He almost glared at his father. &quot;Now promise me, they will leave her alone.&quot;<br>
At least if he could get some sort of promise that the Gods would not harm Serena.  He could have that peace.  Even if his heart was shattered. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=madmartigan>Madmartigan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(7/27/01 10:54:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Watcher</span><hr size=1> ::Madmartigan watched what was going on intently to make sure he cought everying that was said. He kept quiet as he gathered as much information as he could.::<br>
